# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
initially we have number of open bracket is n and closed is also n.

now we can add '(' in the resultant string(i.e s) without any condition and Decrease the count for this and make the recursive call.

but to add ')' in the resultant string there is a condition. the condition is  we can  add ')'  only when the no of open bracket (i.e noOfOpenBracket) is less then the no of closed bracket
 (i.e noOfCloseBracket) because all the closed bracket should make  pair with corresponding open bracket.

means  for n=3 the string "( ) ****)**** ( ( )" is not valid beacuse  the 2nd closed bracket doesn't have the corresponding open bracket before it

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    vector<string> ans;
    void workfunc(int noOfOpenBracket,int noOfCloseBracket,string s)
    {
        if(noOfOpenBracket==0 && noOfCloseBracket==0)
        {
            ans.push_back(s);
            return;
        }
        if(noOfOpenBracket<noOfCloseBracket)
        {
            workfunc(noOfOpenBracket,noOfCloseBracket-1,s+')');
        }
        if(noOfOpenBracket>0)
        workfunc(noOfOpenBracket-1,noOfCloseBracket,s+'(');
    }

public:
    vector<string> generateParenthesis(int n) {
        workfunc(n,n,"");
        return ans;
