Let's define cntLeft as the number of '(' met so far, cntRight as the number of  ')' met so far.

There is an **invariant** that a valid combination of parenthesis alwas hold **cntLeft >= cntRight**.

```
    public List<String> generateParenthesis(int n) {

        List<String> result = new LinkedList<>();
        generateParenthesisFrom(n, 0, 0, new StringBuilder(), result);

        return result;
    }

    private void generateParenthesisFrom(int n, int cntLeft, int cntRight, StringBuilder temp, List<String> result) {

        if (cntLeft > n || cntRight > n || cntLeft < cntRight) {
            return;
        }       
        if ((cntLeft == n) && (cntRight == n)) {
            result.add(temp.toString());
            return;
        }

        temp.append("(");
        generateParenthesisFrom(n, cntLeft + 1, cntRight, temp, result);
        temp.deleteCharAt(temp.length() - 1);      

        temp.append(")");
        generateParenthesisFrom(n, cntLeft, cntRight + 1, temp, result);
        temp.deleteCharAt(temp.length() - 1);
    }
```
