Let me write that out with an example. I use `_()_` to denote which pair of brackets was newly introduced.

take `n=2`. (A)`(())` and (B) `()()`.

(A) becomes: `_()_(())`,  `(_()_())` and `((_()_))`. Thats where we stop because after the last insertion, we run into the first closing bracket
(B) becomes: `_()_()()` and `(_()_)()`. Thats where we stop, again, because there is a closing bracket next.

It runs pretty damn fast. The code is here (can be written for better space but wanted to keep it readable for discussion here).

